festival.introText:
Summer Sound Music Festival returns to Guisborough with a full weekend of live entertainment from the UK's best tribute bands and artists on Friday 28th, Saturday 29th and Sunday 30th July 2023.

 

This is the festival's 10th anniversary at their new bigger location with more entertainment, bigger production and an extra day.

 

On Friday 28th July they bring you a massive 80's Retro Party hosted by world famous DJ Murray Mint featuring tributes to Duran Duran (full live band), Michael Jackson, Wham & George Michael, Madonna and Boy George.

 

On Saturday 29th July they bring you the main event with a host of Rock & Pop Legendsincluding tributes to Queen, Stereophonics, UB40, Pink, The Jam, Robbie Williams and more.

 

On Sunday 30th July they introduce a new addition to the festival... a Summer Sound Kidz Concert with a full day of pop tributes for all the family with no age restrictions. The line-up includes tributes to Little Mix, Dua Lipa, Lady Gaga, Ed Sheeran and Pink.

 

It's a weekend you'll never forget with funfair, fireworks, street entertainers, festival stalls, cocktail bars, street food and more.

 

 

Tickets on sale from 9am Friday 27th January.

faqs.question: When is Summer Sound Music Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Summer Sound Music Festival takes place on Friday 28th - Sunday 30th July, 2023

faqs.question: Is there any parking at Summer Sound Music Festival?
faqs.answer: There is no car parking on site. We advise anyone travelling by car to park in the town centre. A free shuttle bus will be available from The Fox Inn which will take you directly to the entrance.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Where is Summer Sound Music Festival?
faqs.answer: Summer Sound Music Festival will be held at Guisborough Rugby Club, Belmangate, Guisborough, TS14 7BB.

faqs.question: Does Summer Sound Music Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
Over 16´s may attend but only when accompanied by an adult. One adult may bring in 2 over 16's. The bars will be operating a challenge 25 policy to prevent underage drinking. You may be asked for a valid photo ID.

 

Sunday's event is all ages!

faqs.question: What can I bring into Summer Sound Music Festival?
faqs.answer:
You are allowed to bring your own food and drink. A sensible alcohol limit will be in place at the discretion of the security. A one-hand limit will be in place so please only bring what you can carry in one hand. Any excessive amounts will be confiscated on entry and available to collect when you leave. Please note food and a licensed bar will be available on site.

You can bring your own camping chairs but these need to be taken away at the end of the night.

Same rules apply as previous years regarding food and drink. Only reasonable amounts are allowed in, 4-6 cans per person (recommended) and no crates or bottles of spirits. Glass is not allowed on site so plastic bottles and cans only.

You can bring your own food but remember we have various traders on site offering a wide range of street food including hog roast, wood fired pizza, chinese noodles, traditional burgers, crispy chicken wraps, loaded fries, hot dogs and more.

faqs.question: Are there any other restrictions on what I can bring into Summer Sound Music Festival?
faqs.answer:
Gazebos are only allowed if you have pre-booked a space. Spaces are limited and gazebo tickets can be purchased on this site. Gazebos can be no bigger than 3m x 3m and must be removed at the end of the night.

Gazebo ticket holders can access the site 1 hour earlier to erect their gazebos. Anyone entering the site must have a valid ticket.

Any chairs brought onto the site must be removed at the end of the night.

Bags will be searched upon entry and any glass bottles will be retained.

Portable/throw away BBQ’s are not allowed.

Chinese lanterns are not allowed.

No glass bottles, metal cutlery or crockery are allowed into the site. Please bring plastic containers, plastic cutlery and paper plates only.

faqs.question: What drinks/alcohol is served at Summer Sound Music Festival?
faqs.answer: We have bars on site serving draught beers and lagers, wines, spirits and cocktails, so don't worry about not bringing enough.
